            },
            "description": "Monitor executed commands and arguments for commands that can be used to disable logging. For example, Wevtutil, auditpol, sc stop EventLog, reg add, Set- or Stop-Service, Set- or New-ItemProperty, sc config, and offensive tooling (such as Mimikatz and Invoke-Phant0m) may be used to clear logs and/or change the EventLog/audit policy."
